INSERT INTO `movie` VALUES (0000000001,'The Shawshank Redemption','Over the course of several years, two convicts form a friendship, seeking consolation and, eventually, redemption through basic compassion. Andy Dufresne, a banker sentenced to life in prison, befriends fellow inmate Ellis \"Red\" Redding and gradually earns his trust. Despite his challenging circumstances, Andy uses his intelligence and perseverance to improve the lives of his fellow prisoners and ultimately orchestrates a dramatic escape that changes everything.','image1.jpg','The Shawshank Redemption is a 1994 American prison drama film written and directed by Frank Darabont, based on the 1982 Stephen King novella Rita Hayworth and Shawshank Redemption. The film tells the story of banker Andy Dufresne (Tim Robbins), who is sentenced to life in Shawshank State Penitentiary for the murders of his wife and her lover, despite his claims of innocence. Over the following two decades, he befriends a fellow prisoner, contraband smuggler Ellis \"Red\" Redding (Morgan Freeman), and becomes instrumental in a money laundering operation led by the prison warden Samuel Norton (Bob Gunton). William Sadler, Clancy Brown, Gil Bellows, and James Whitmore appear in supporting roles.'),(0000000001,'The Godfather','The aging patriarch of an organized crime dynasty transfers control of his clandestine empire to his reluctant son. Michael Corleone, who initially wants nothing to do with the family business, becomes deeply involved in the violent underworld after a series of personal and professional betrayals. The film explores themes of power, loyalty, and the impact of organized crime on family and society.','image2.jpg','The Godfather is a 1972 American crime film directed by Francis Ford Coppola, who co-wrote the screenplay with Mario Puzo, based on Puzo\'s best-selling 1969 novel of the same name. The film stars Marlon Brando, Al Pacino, James Caan, Richard S. Castellano, Robert Duvall, Sterling Hayden, John Marley, Richard Conte, and Diane Keaton. It is the first installment in The Godfather trilogy. The story, spanning from 1945 to 1955, chronicles the Corleone family under patriarch Vito Corleone (Brando), focusing on the transformation of his youngest son, Michael Corleone (Pacino), from reluctant family outsider to ruthless mafia boss.'),(0000000001,'The Dark Knight','When the menace known as the Joker wreaks havoc and chaos on the people of Gotham, Batman must accept one of the greatest psychological and physical tests of his ability to fight injustice. The Joker’s plan is to destroy Batman’s reputation and bring Gotham City to its knees, forcing Batman, with the help of his allies, to confront his deepest fears and moral dilemmas.','image3.jpg','The Dark Knight is a 2008 superhero film directed by Christopher Nolan, who co-wrote the screenplay with his brother Jonathan Nolan. Based on the DC Comics character Batman, it is the sequel to Batman Begins (2005) and the second installment in The Dark Knight Trilogy. The film stars Christian Bale as Bruce Wayne / Batman, alongside Michael Caine, Heath Ledger, Gary Oldman, Aaron Eckhart, Maggie Gyllenhaal, and Morgan Freeman. In the film, Bruce Wayne / Batman forms an alliance with Police Lieutenant James Gordon (Oldman) and District Attorney Harvey Dent (Eckhart) to dismantle organized crime in Gotham City, but their efforts are thwarted by the intervention of the anarchistic Joker (Ledger), who seeks to undermine Batman\'s influence and throw the city into anarchy.'),(0000000001,'12 Angry Men','The jury in a New York City murder trial is frustrated by a single member whose skeptical caution forces them to more carefully consider the evidence before jumping to a hasty verdict. Each juror brings their personal biases and experiences to the deliberations, which exposes their prejudices and ultimately challenges the notion of justice in the American legal system.','image4.jpg','12 Angry Men is a 1957 American courtroom drama film directed by Sidney Lumet. Adapted from a teleplay of the same name by Reginald Rose, it stars Henry Fonda (who also produced), Lee J. Cobb, Ed Begley, E. G. Marshall, Jack Warden, and Jack Klugman. The film tells the story of a jury of 12 men as they deliberate the conviction or acquittal of a defendant on the basis of reasonable doubt, forcing the jurors to question their morals and values. It is noted for its almost exclusive use of one set, where the entire film takes place, and its exploration of the role of moral integrity in the American justice system.'),(0000000001,'Schindler\'s List','In German-occupied Poland during World War II, industrialist Oskar Schindler gradually becomes concerned for his Jewish workforce after witnessing their persecution by the Nazis. His transformation from a profit-driven businessman to a humanitarian who saves over a thousand Jews is depicted through harrowing and emotional sequences that highlight the horrors of the Holocaust and the impact of individual bravery.','image5.jpg','Schindler\'s List is a 1993 American epic historical drama film directed and produced by Steven Spielberg and written by Steven Zaillian. It is based on the 1982 non-fiction novel Schindler\'s Ark by Australian novelist Thomas Keneally. The film follows Oskar Schindler (Liam Neeson), a German industrialist and member of the Nazi Party, who is credited with saving the lives of 1,200 Jews during the Holocaust by employing them in his factories. The film features Ralph Fiennes as SS officer Amon Göth and Ben Kingsley as Schindler\'s Jewish accountant Itzhak Stern.'),(0000000001,'Inception','A skilled thief, who steals secrets from deep within the subconscious during the dream state, is offered a chance to have his criminal history erased in exchange for implanting an idea into the mind of a target. This mind-bending heist film delves into the complexities of dreams, reality, and the human psyche, creating a visually stunning and intellectually stimulating experience.','image6.jpg','Inception is a 2010 science fiction film written and directed by Christopher Nolan. The film stars Leonardo DiCaprio as Dom Cobb, a thief who enters the dreams of others to steal secrets and ideas. Cobb is given a chance to redeem his past crimes if he can successfully perform an inception—implanting an idea into the mind of a target without them realizing it. The film also features an ensemble cast including Joseph Gordon-Levitt, Ellen Page, Tom Hardy, and Marion Cotillard. Inception is renowned for its complex narrative structure and innovative visual effects.'),(0000000001,'The Matrix','In a dystopian future where humanity is unknowingly trapped inside a simulated reality created by intelligent machines, a computer hacker discovers the truth and joins a group of rebels fighting to free humanity from its artificial imprisonment. The film blends philosophical questions with groundbreaking special effects and action sequences, challenging perceptions of reality and existence.','image7.jpg','The Matrix is a 1999 science fiction film written and directed by the Wachowskis. The film stars Keanu Reeves as Neo, a computer hacker who learns that the world he lives in is a simulated reality created by sentient machines. With the help of the rebel leader Morpheus (Laurence Fishburne) and the mysterious Trinity (Carrie-Anne Moss), Neo fights to liberate humanity from the Matrix and discover his true potential. The film is known for its innovative special effects, including the iconic \"bullet time\" sequences, and its exploration of themes related to reality and consciousness.'),(0000000001,'Fight Club','An insomniac office worker forms an underground fight club with a soap salesman, which becomes a radical anti-consumerist organization. As the club evolves, the protagonist struggles with his own identity and the consequences of his actions, leading to a shocking and memorable twist that questions the nature of self and societal norms.','image8.jpg','Fight Club is a 1999 film directed by David Fincher and based on the novel by Chuck Palahniuk. The film stars Edward Norton as the unnamed narrator and Brad Pitt as Tyler Durden, a charismatic soap salesman who forms an underground fight club with the narrator. The film explores themes of masculinity, consumerism, and mental health, and is known for its dark humor, innovative storytelling, and a significant plot twist that challenges the audience’s perceptions.'),(0000000001,'Pulp Fiction','The lives of several individuals intersect in a series of violent and comedic vignettes that explore themes of redemption, fate, and the absurdity of life. The film’s non-linear narrative structure and memorable dialogue contribute to its status as a groundbreaking work in modern cinema, showcasing director Quentin Tarantino’s distinctive style.','image9.jpg','Pulp Fiction is a 1994 film directed by Quentin Tarantino. It features an ensemble cast including John Travolta, Uma Thurman, Samuel L. Jackson, and Bruce Willis. The film is known for its non-linear narrative, interweaving multiple storylines involving crime and violence. The film’s sharp dialogue, eclectic soundtrack, and unique structure have made it a landmark in independent cinema and popular culture.'),(0000000001,'The Lord of the Rings: The Fellowship of the Ring','In a quest to destroy a powerful ring and prevent the dark lord Sauron from conquering Middle-earth, a diverse group of heroes forms a fellowship to journey across dangerous lands. The film combines epic fantasy with rich character development and breathtaking visuals, setting the stage for an epic trilogy.','image10.jpg','The Lord of the Rings: The Fellowship of the Ring is a 2001 fantasy film directed by Peter Jackson, based on J.R.R. Tolkien’s novel. The film follows the journey of Frodo Baggins (Elijah Wood) and a fellowship of companions as they set out to destroy the One Ring and thwart the dark lord Sauron. The film features an ensemble cast including Ian McKellen, Viggo Mortensen, and Liv Tyler. Known for its epic storytelling, groundbreaking special effects, and detailed world-building, it is the first installment in The Lord of the Rings trilogy.'),(0000000001,'Gladiator','A betrayed Roman general seeks vengeance against the corrupt emperor who murdered his family and stole his honor. The film combines epic battle scenes with a powerful story of revenge and redemption, highlighting the struggles of a fallen hero fighting for justice and recognition in a brutal empire.','image11.jpg','Gladiator is a 2000 historical epic film directed by Ridley Scott, starring Russell Crowe as Maximus Decimus Meridius, a betrayed Roman general who seeks revenge against Emperor Commodus (Joaquin Phoenix). The film’s grand scale and intense action sequences are matched by a deeply emotional narrative that explores themes of loyalty, honor, and justice. The film won multiple awards, including the Academy Award for Best Picture.'),(0000000001,'Casablanca','During World War II, an American expatriate meets a former lover and must choose between helping her and her husband escape from the Nazis or rekindling their romance. The film’s blend of romance, political intrigue, and memorable dialogue has cemented its status as a classic of American cinema.','image12.jpg','Casablanca is a 1942 romantic drama film directed by Michael Curtiz. Starring Humphrey Bogart and Ingrid Bergman, the film is set in Vichy-controlled Casablanca during World War II. The story revolves around Rick Blaine (Bogart), a nightclub owner who must choose between his love for Ilsa Lund (Bergman) and helping her and her husband escape from the Nazis. The film is celebrated for its memorable lines, iconic performances, and its blend of romance and wartime drama.'),(0000000001,'The Silence of the Lambs','A young FBI trainee seeks the help of an imprisoned cannibalistic serial killer to catch another killer on the loose. The psychological cat-and-mouse game between the trainee and the cannibal provides a gripping narrative filled with tension, horror, and unexpected twists.','image13.jpg','The Silence of the Lambs is a 1991 psychological horror film directed by Jonathan Demme, based on the novel by Thomas Harris. It stars Jodie Foster as Clarice Starling, an FBI trainee who consults with Dr. Hannibal Lecter (Anthony Hopkins), a brilliant but dangerous cannibalistic serial killer, to apprehend another serial killer. The film won several Academy Awards, including Best Picture, Best Director, Best Actor for Hopkins, and Best Actress for Foster.'),(0000000001,'Se7en','Two detectives hunt a serial killer who uses the seven deadly sins as his modus operandi. As the investigation unfolds, the detectives are drawn into a chilling and complex plot that leads to a shocking climax, revealing the true nature of the killer’s plan.','image14.jpg','Se7en is a 1995 crime thriller film directed by David Fincher, starring Brad Pitt and Morgan Freeman as detectives investigating a series of murders based on the seven deadly sins. The film is known for its dark, atmospheric tone and a plot that builds to a disturbing and memorable conclusion. It explores themes of justice, morality, and the nature of evil.'),(0000000001,'The Departed','An undercover cop and a mole within the police force attempt to identify each other while infiltrating the Boston mob. The intense cat-and-mouse game between the two leads to a thrilling climax, exposing the complexities of loyalty and deception within the world of crime and law enforcement.','image15.jpg','The Departed is a 2006 crime thriller directed by Martin Scorsese, featuring Leonardo DiCaprio, Matt Damon, and Jack Nicholson. The film follows an undercover cop who infiltrates the mob while a mole within the police tries to expose him. The intricate plot and strong performances make it a gripping examination of crime, betrayal, and identity. The film won several Academy Awards, including Best Picture and Best Director.'),(0000000001,'Whiplash','An ambitious young drummer enrolls in a prestigious music conservatory and clashes with an abusive instructor who pushes him to the brink of his abilities. The intense struggle between student and teacher explores themes of perfectionism, ambition, and the pursuit of greatness.','image16.jpg','Whiplash is a 2014 drama film directed by Damien Chazelle. The film stars Miles Teller as Andrew Neiman, a young and talented drummer who aspires to greatness under the tutelage of a ruthless music instructor, Fletcher (J.K. Simmons). The film examines the sacrifices and pressures involved in achieving excellence, with a focus on the demanding and often abusive nature of the teacher-student relationship. J.K. Simmons won the Academy Award for Best Supporting Actor for his role.'),(0000000001,'The Revenant','A frontiersman on a quest for survival after being left for dead by his own hunting team encounters numerous challenges and adversaries. His struggle for vengeance against those who betrayed him drives a harrowing narrative of endurance and survival in the harsh wilderness.','image17.jpg','The Revenant is a 2015 survival drama directed by Alejandro G. Iñárritu. The film stars Leonardo DiCaprio as Hugh Glass, a frontiersman who embarks on a grueling journey of survival and revenge after being abandoned by his expedition team. The film is renowned for its stunning cinematography, intense performances, and its portrayal of the brutal and unforgiving natural environment.'),(0000000001,'Joker','A troubled comedian living in Gotham City transforms into the infamous Joker, a figure of chaos and anarchy. The film explores his descent into madness and the impact of societal neglect and personal trauma on his transformation into a symbol of resistance against a fractured society.','image18.jpg','Joker is a 2019 psychological thriller directed by Todd Phillips and starring Joaquin Phoenix as Arthur Fleck, a failed comedian who becomes the criminal mastermind known as the Joker. The film delves into the character’s troubled past and the social conditions that contribute to his descent into madness. It received critical acclaim for Phoenix’s performance and its dark, thought-provoking narrative.'),(0000000001,'Parasite','A poor family schemes to infiltrate the lives of a wealthy household by posing as unrelated, qualified individuals. The film skillfully blends social satire, drama, and suspense to critique class inequality and the lengths people will go to improve their circumstances.','image19.jpg','Parasite is a 2019 South Korean dark comedy thriller directed by Bong Joon-ho. The film follows the Kim family, who cunningly infiltrate the lives of the affluent Park family by posing as unrelated professionals. The story explores themes of class disparity, greed, and social mobility, culminating in a dramatic and unexpected conclusion. The film won the Palme d\'Or at the Cannes Film Festival and several Academy Awards, including Best Picture.'),(0000000001,'Spirited Away','A young girl stumbles into a mysterious world of spirits and deities after her parents are transformed into pigs. As she navigates this strange realm, she must confront her own fears and find a way to rescue her parents, learning about courage, perseverance, and self-discovery along the way.','image20.jpg','Spirited Away is a 2001 Japanese animated fantasy film directed by Hayao Miyazaki and produced by Studio Ghibli. The film follows Chihiro, a young girl who becomes trapped in a magical world while her parents are transformed into pigs. To save her parents and return to her own world, Chihiro must work in a mysterious bathhouse run by spirits and gods. The film is renowned for its imaginative storytelling, stunning animation, and exploration of themes related to identity and transformation.');
